obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1982  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: congenital myasthenic syndrome patient has a E59K mutation in the nAChR delta subunit.\nFig.2+3+4: The mutation was shown to affect channel kinetics with heterologous expression of WT and δE59K mutant receptors in HEK cells.\n\nNote: data to support the action of this mutation in situ is not included in this paper, but the annotation to the term 'transmitter-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential (GO:1904315)' is based on the presence the myasthenic syndrome in the mutation carrier and the well established localization of the nAChR in the postsynaptic membrane of muscle fibers.. Experimental description: Data is on heterologously expressed receptors of human species; \"Because the patient phenotype suggested an effect of the mutations in utero as well as on mature muscle, we investigated functional effects of the δ subunit mutations on both fetal- and adult-type human AChR. cDNAs encoding mutant δ subunits in combination with wild-type α, β, ε, or γ were transfected into HEK293 cells, and cell surface 125I-α-BuTx was measured\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1982" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

